      • generateConcreteTokenization

        public static edu.jhu.hlt.concrete.Concrete.Tokenization generateConcreteTokenization(java.util.List<java.lang.String> tokens,
                                                                      java.util.List<java.lang.String> tokenTags,
                                                                      int[] offsets,
                                                                      int startPos)
        Generate a Concrete.Tokenization object from a list of tokens, list of tags, list of offsets, and start position of the text (e.g., first text character in the text). Assumes tags are part of speech tags. Invokes generateConcreteTokenization(List, int[], int) then adds tagging.
        Parameters:
        tokens - - a List of tokens (Strings)
        offsets - - an array of integers (offsets)
        startPos - - starting position of the text
        Returns:
        a Concrete.Tokenization object with correct tokenization and token tagging
        See Also:
        generateConcreteTokenization(List, int[], int)
